HiddenLayer is now defending a patent-infringement suit filed by Congruent Media Resourcing LLC in W.D. Tex. before Judge Walter David Counts III. The complaint asserts U.S. Patent No. 9,135,418, and the plaintiff's structure, a shell-style multi-word LLC, fits a familiar NPE pattern: file in a favorable venue, assert a single patent, and pressure a settlement before the defendant can build a strong invalidity record.

The one-year IPR bar starts running from service, and W.D. Tex. dockets move. Stilta can deliver a focused prior-art and invalidity analysis on the asserted patent quickly, giving your team the evidence it needs to evaluate PTAB options and inform claim-construction strategy before the schedule tightens.

If it would be useful, we can send a short overview of how Stilta approaches single-patent NPE matters. Just reply here and we will get it to you.

